SIMPLE: hardihood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hardihood
<hw>Har"di*hood</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧r"d⟦icr⟧*h⟦oocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hardy</ets> + <ets>-hood</ets>.]</ety> <def>Boldness, united
with firmness and constancy of mind; bravery; intrepidity; also,
audaciousness; impudence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A bound of graceful <qex>hardihood</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is the society of numbers which gives <qex>hardihood</qex> to
iniquity.</q> <rj><qau>Buckminster.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Intrepidity; courage; pluck; resolution;
stoutness; audacity; effrontery; impudence.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hardily</ent>⟦br⟧
